cs.RO, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.SY, cs.LG 

Reasoning: 
- cs.RO (Robotics) is the most likely category as the paper proposes a navigation algorithm for a mobile robot. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision) is also likely as the algorithm is based on visual features and aims to improve visual localization. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the algorithm uses artificial potential fields to generate control actions. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is a possible category as the paper deals with controlling a mobile robot. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is less likely as the paper does not explicitly mention any machine learning techniques.
